        </disp-formula>
        <p>The output data frame of <monospace>smatrix()</monospace> is a square matrix with the actors in the column and reactors in the row (<xref rid="pone.0271337.g003" ref-type="fig">Fig 3A</xref>) and the output of <monospace>dmatrix()</monospace> is a square matrix containing the dyadic dominance relationship (<xref rid="pone.0271337.g003" ref-type="fig">Fig 3B</xref>).</p>
